<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-780-240  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 780 240.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Information Executive  Summer 1990 v3 n3 p37(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Controlling the integrated information web.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Cloud, Avery C.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The data processing manager must consider all aspects ofinformation, including how it flows through the company.andP;  Onetechnique is integrated information control, a system of standardsand procedures for handling the flow of information through thecompany and through its various forms.andP;  The control elements aresecurity, recoverability, privacy, availability, and accuracy.andO;Efficient and effective flow of information between storage andprocessing points is provided by integrated processing strategies.andO;The control standards and procedures should be divided intohierarchical levels.andP;  Corporate level creates and maintainscompany-wide standards for information resource control.andP;  MISlevel develops physical and data security procedures.andP;  Departmentlevel develops departmental policies, procedures, and practices.andO;Distributed application level manages and measures howsuccessfully each application is being controlled.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Information SystemsManagement of EDPIntegrated SystemsControl Systems.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   The corporate information web. (chart)Network order processing. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>